3.4 Formal vs Informal Sector Classification
For Singapore, the basis of selection of hawker-origin vendors revolves around the understanding that most Singapore citizens do not constantly approach formal restaurants for meals. Instead, Singapore’s hawker centres are seen to be the heart of the nation. Most Singapore citizens prefer hawker food due to their low cost, quality and personal relationships with the hawker vendors. As such, a large proportion of consumer expenditure is not captured by the formal sector. Thus, the informal price sector has genuine contributions that can be made to the Consumer Price Index (CPI), allowing for a more comprehensive evaluation and approximation of the consumer price index through algorithms. 
